Now the city of God is called in the Hebrew Jerusalem and its name when
translated is ‘vision of peace’. Therefore, do not seek for the city of the
Existent among the regions of the earth, since it is not wrought of wood or
stone, but in a soul, in which there is no warring, whose sight is keen, which
has set before it as its aim to live in contemplation and peace.
